article.headline: Birt, Woodard lead Tulsa to 74-55 win over Temple

images.name: D. Dingle made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by J. Bond.
images.caption: 1H (17:11) TEM Daniel Dingle made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Jaylen Bond.

article.linkText: Birt, Woodard lead Tulsa to 74-55 win over Temple
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Pat Birt scored 23 and James Woodard added 15 points, a career-high eight assists and six rebounds to help Tulsa beat Temple 74-55 Tuesday night. The Golden Hurricane won its third in a row and pulled within a game of American Athletic Conference-leading Temple. Marquel Curtis finished with 13 points for Tulsa (19-9, 11-5). A layup by Curtis with 7:13 to play capped a 13-2 run and put the Golden Hurricane up 60-46. Temple (17-10, 11-4) trailed by double figures the rest of the way. The Owls led 25-13 before Tulsa closed the first half with an 18-4 run. Obi Enechionyia led Temple with 17 points, including four 3-pointers, and three blocked shots. Quenton DeCosey scored 11 with nine rebounds. Tulsa committed just six turnovers and outscored the Owls 10-0 on fast-break points.
